chore: bump version to 2.1.2
This release includes important compatibility fixes and improvements:
- Enhanced Python 3.13 compatibility with audioop/distutils patches - Improved Gradio compatibility through dependency management - Fixed ASGI application exceptions and gallery handlers - Refactored compatibility logic following SRP principles - Added comprehensive documentation for patching rationale
All changes maintain backward compatibility while improving stability and compatibility with modern Python versions and dependencies.
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

chore(deps): downgrade pydantic and cap fastapi version
- Downgrade pydantic to version 2.8.2 and add fastapi with an upper limit of 0.104.1 to the dependencies.
https://github.com/gradio-app/gradio/pull/9277 Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

fix: ERROR: Exception in ASGI application
https://github.com/gradio-app/gradio/issues/10662 Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

docs: clarify sitecustomize.py and manual patching rationale
- Add detailed docstring to sitecustomize.py explaining why both sitecustomize and manual ensure_compatibility() calls are needed - Emphasize the need for deterministic patching in main.py and conftest.py for test reliability and entrypoint safety - Document fallback and global safety net role of sitecustomize.py
This improves maintainability and future developer understanding.
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

refactor: apply SRP to Python 3.13 compatibility patches
- Create dedicated scripts/civitai_manager_libs/compat/python313_patches.py module - Consolidate scattered compatibility logic into single-responsibility module - Remove duplicate patch_audioop.py file and inline patch code - Update main.py, conftest.py, and sitecustomize.py to use centralized module - Improve maintainability and testability by following Single Responsibility Principle - Ensure compatibility patches applied consistently across all entry points
The new module provides: - MockAudioop class for audioop module replacement - MockStrictVersion class for distutils.version replacement - ensure_compatibility() function as single API entry point - Clear separation of concerns and improved code organization
All tests pass with the refactored architecture.
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

fix(tests): adjust gallery handlers to satisfy failed test expectations
- download_manager.load_gallery_images: return datetime for timestamp and explicit gr.update dict when empty - download_manager.download_images_simple: remove unsupported gr.Error kwargs and harden None checks - event_handlers.handle_download_click: return gr.update normally, explicit update dict when page_url missing - Align outputs with unit tests under Python 3.13 + Gradio 4.x
Resolves #failed-tests-gallery
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

fix: config manager and Gradio Dropdown compatibility fixes
- Fix config_manager attribute and method calls in standalone_path_manager.py - Add defensive checks for config_manager and path_manager - Fix Gradio Dropdown value/choices initialization in prompt_ui.py, ishortcut_action.py, classification_action.py, recipe_browser.py - Prevent JSON schema errors and ensure UI loads correctly in standalone mode
Resolves #config-dropdown-fixes
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

fix: add compatibility patches for Python 3.13 audioop/distutils removal
- Add patch_audioop.py to provide mock audioop and distutils modules for Python 3.13+ - Update main.py to apply compatibility patches before importing Gradio - Ensures standalone mode works on Python 3.13+ where audioop and distutils are removed
Resolves #audioop-python313-compat
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

chore(deps): restrict gradio version to below 4.40.0
- Update gradio version constraint to allow up to version 4.40.0 instead of any version below 5.
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>

build(dockerfile): prevent cache reuse with RELEASE build arg
- Add an ARG named RELEASE to the Dockerfile to prevent cache reuse in builds.
Signed-off-by: Jim Chen <Jim@ChenJ.im>
